UIText.Guide_23_1.1: Short on supplies? Sometimes you can synthesize what you need—let's go over how it works.
UIText.Guide_23_3.1: Select the required recipe to craft the item.
UIText.Guide_23_4.1: Select here to view the target item's details.
UIText.Guide_23_5.1: Select here to see the material details. Give it a try!
UIText.Guide_24_1.1: It's time to introduce you to the Trekker Commission. I'll guide you through it!
UIText.Guide_24_2.1: Send Trekkers out on commissions to earn rewards!
UIText.Guide_24_3.1: Different commissions have different squad requirements—make sure you meet them before you set off!
UIText.Guide_24_4.1: Let's dispatch your first commission now!
UIText.Guide_24_5.1: Confirm the duration, and the commission will begin!
UIText.Guide_25_1.1: Discs boost your entire squad during Monolith explorations. Leveling them up further improves these buffs.
UIText.Guide_25_2.1: When the Disc is equipped in the main slot, the Melody Skill will be activated.
UIText.Guide_25_3.1: The Harmony Skill, on the other hand, requires a certain type and amount of Musical Notes to activate.Musical Notes can be collected during Monolith exploration.
UIText.Guide_26_1.1:
Boss, you have made progress in your Power.
Open [Missions] for more details.
UIText.Guide_27_1.1: You've just obtained some more powerful Discs. Go ahead and equip one.
UIText.Guide_27_2.1: Select here to confirm the Disc's effect.
UIText.Guide_28_1.1: Discs equipped in support slots also offer bonus effects, but their Disc Skills will remain inactive.
UIText.Guide_28_2.1: Support Discs grant extra Musical Notes right at the start of an exploration. They can improve the efficiency of the build when properly paired.
UIText.Guide_28_3.1: Besides, you can gradually unlock more support Disc slots through [Monolith Research]!All set? Time to move out!
UIText.Guide_29_1.1: These are the Musical Notes in the Monolith. Each type of Musical Note offers a different bonus effect, which can be improved when you collect more of them.
UIText.Guide_29_2.1: Select here to check your current Musical Note collection.
UIText.Guide_2_1.1: Before you set off, how about recruiting a Trekker to join your adventure? Having some trusty company along would be great.
UIText.Guide_2_2.1: You can perform [Recruit x10] up to 20 times on the Beginner Limited Banner and save 5 results. Pick any saved result to begin your journey.
UIText.Guide_2_3.1: You can recruit now or after completing all the tutorials.
UIText.Guide_32_1.1: Here are all the Musical Notes collected during this Ascension.
UIText.Guide_32_2.1: Each Harmony Skill requires a specific set of Musical Notes to activate.
UIText.Guide_32_3.1:
You need to re-collect Musical Notes in each Ascension.
Musical Notes and Harmony Skills are inseparable components for setting new Records.
UIText.Guide_32_4.1: Collect as many powerful Musical Note combination as you can during your Ascension.
UIText.Guide_3_1.1: You haven't finished your recruitments in the Beginner Limited Banner. After completing the tutorials, you can return and recruit more. Continue your journey now and recruit later?
UIText.Guide_41_1.1: Select [Trekker] to view Trekker details and level them up.
UIText.Guide_42_1.1: Select [Story] to continue with the main story.
UIText.Guide_42_2.1: Select [Main Story] to continue your adventure.Or, you can go on with your Monolith exploration or challenges of other modes.
UIText.Guide_43_1.1: You can use [Heartlink] to message Trekkers you've befriended. This is the key feature of a cellphone.
UIText.Guide_43_2.1: Select the portrait to view messages from Trekkers.
UIText.Guide_43_3.1: Switch to [Invite] to select Trekkers you've befriended and invite them to join your journey. Note that you can only invite Trekkers with the required Affinity Level.
UIText.Guide_43_4.1: Select [Mail] to send a gift, increasing the Affinity of the chosen Trekker.
UIText.Guide_44_1.1: As a newcomer, joining more events will help you improve faster.Select [Events] to check what's going on.
UIText.Guide_45_1.1: When a Trekker reaches a certain level, you need to increase their rank to further their development.
UIText.Guide_45_2.1: Tiering up the Trekkers will also improve their base stats and the level cap of their skills.
UIText.Guide_45_3.1: Materials required for tiering up a Trekker need to be obtained through [Tier-up Trial] of a certain kind.
UIText.Guide_45_4.1: Try to use the materials you obtained to tier up.
UIText.Guide_46_1.1: This Trekker's Level Cap has been increased to Level 20.
UIText.Guide_46_3.1: Upon reaching Tier 3, Trekkers can unlock their Awakened Appearance.
UIText.Guide_47_1.1: Finally ... the key to the stairs to the stars has been cracked. You can now use the Monolith Stairs Pass to complete the Ascension in no time.
UIText.Guide_47_3.1: Select a Monolith of any Element.
UIText.Guide_48_1.1: You can see how many Monolith Stairs Passes you own here.
UIText.Guide_48_2.1: You must clear one Monolith of the corresponding difficulty before using the Monolith Stairs Pass!
UIText.Guide_48_3.1: With the Monolith Stairs Pass, you can breeze through Monoliths to get the best Records.
UIText.Guide_49_1.1: Each Trekker has different combat styles and a unique set of abilities.When fighting as the main Trekker, a Trekker can activate Auto Attacks.
UIText.Guide_49_2.1: Also, when fighting as the main Trekker, a Trekker can activate their Main Skill.
UIText.Guide_49_3.1: And when fighting as a support Trekker, a Trekker can activate their Support Skill.
UIText.Guide_49_4.1: Whether the main Trekker or a support Trekker, a Trekker can activate their Ultimate. Casting the Ultimate consumes Energy, which slowly recovers during the battle.
UIText.Guide_49_5.1: Targeted enhancement of Trekker abilities can actively improve your battle performance and influence even previous records.
UIText.Guide_49_6.1: Upgrading Trekker skills costs Skill Cartridges of a certain kind, which can be obtained through Skill Trials.
UIText.Guide_4_10.1: Noya and I will be responsible for <color=#EA5946>Support</color> and provide combat assistance to the <color=#EA5946>Main</color> during the exploration.
UIText.Guide_4_12.1: After getting the squad ready, we can get your Discs in order!
UIText.Guide_4_13.1: Besides building a line-up on your own, you can also select [Auto-deploy], and the system will select suitable Trekkers for the current Monolith for you.
UIText.Guide_4_2.1: The New Star Guild is still just getting started. Let's try exploring <color=#EA5946>Misstep On One</color> first.
UIText.Guide_4_4.1:
Before you start exploring, assign your squad members! 
Select and open the <color=#EA5946>Squad</color> interface.
UIText.Guide_4_5.1: Select a Trekker's portrait to add them to your squad.
UIText.Guide_4_6.1: <color=#EA5946>Amber</color> is the most agile of the Trekkers. Let's select her and place her in the squad.
UIText.Guide_4_7.1: The first Trekker to be placed in the squad will take the role of the <color=#EA5946>Main</color>, and lead the squad as the squad leader.
UIText.Guide_4_8.1: Then, add me, <color=#EA5946>Iris,</color> to the squad.
UIText.Guide_4_9.1: Finally, add <color=#EA5946>Noya</color> to the squad as well. A squad requires <color=#EA5946>3 Trekkers</color> to be able to start the exploration.
UIText.Guide_50_1.1: Trekkers can activate Contribution Emblems to get Combat Power bonuses.
UIText.Guide_50_2.1: Complete Emblem Trials of corresponding factions to obtain Faction Coins, and use them to activate Contribution Emblems.
UIText.Guide_50_3.1: Spend coins to light up this Emblem.
UIText.Guide_50_4.1: Here you can see the stat boosts you received by activating this Element. Each activation may yield different results.
UIText.Guide_50_5.1: You can equip this Emblem once it's activated. If you're not satisfied with the outcome, use the Emblem Polisher to try activate it again.
UIText.Guide_51_1.1: Affinity Level with the current Trekker is displayed here.
UIText.Guide_51_2.1: You can increase a Trekker's Affinity through completing Companion Targets, gift-giving, or sending invitations.
UIText.Guide_51_3.1: With increased Affinity, the Trekker's combat power will increase slightly, and more archive entries and voiceovers will be unlocked.
UIText.Guide_51_4.1: Increased Affinity level will also unlock the Trekker's personal stories.Finishing the key stories unlocks Memory Snapshots, which can be set as your main screen.
UIText.Guide_5_1.1: The <color=#EA5946>Potentials</color> and <color=#EA5946>Disc Skills</color> activated during this exploration will be saved and generated into a <color=#EA5946>Record</color> that can be used for other battles.
UIText.Guide_5_2.1: The activated <color=#EA5946>Potentials</color> and <color=#EA5946>Disc Skills</color> will affect the <color=#EA5946>Record Rating</color>. The higher the Rating, the stronger the Record.
UIText.Guide_5_3.1: <color=#EA5946>Records</color> are <color=#EA5946>bound</color> to the Trekkers in this exploration. The Record cannot be changed when using it for other battles.
UIText.Guide_5_4.1: Select <color=#EA5946>Save Record</color>.Saved Records can be viewed in <color=#EA5946>Go</color>.
UIText.Guide_6_1.1: Select [Missions] to view targets to be completed.Check them to decide what to do next.
UIText.Guide_6_2.1: Your current Authorization Level is 1.Improve your Authorization Level to unlock more features.
UIText.Guide_6_3.1: Complete targets to receive generous rewards and increase your Authorization Level faster.
UIText.Guide_7_1.1: We need more supplies to keep going.Select <color=#EA5946>Go</color>.
UIText.Guide_7_4.1: Spend Vigor to participate in [Basic Trial] to obtain various crucial supplies.
UIText.Guide_7_5.1: Select here to switch the type of rewards you'll receive.For now, let's stock up on Trekker's Notes to boost Trekker experience!
UIText.Guide_8_1.1: Any action outside Ascension requires using an existing Record.
UIText.Guide_8_2.1: Select to choose a Record set.
UIText.Guide_9_1.1: Complete chapter-specific missions on the Tyrant Growth page to claim rewards and quickly boost your Power.
UIText.Guide_9_2.1: You can also help your guild grow by leveling up to complete targets on the Level Rewards.
UIText.Guide_9_3.1: Select to claim rewards for reaching Authorization Lv. 2.
UIText.Guide_9_4.1: Complete targets and increase your Authorization Level to Lv. 3 to unlock more features!
